snippet.textDisplay: It is truly sad about the lives lost in the Kobe Bryant Helicopter crash incident. However, I think it’s important to examine Kobe’s relationship with his parents. I just don’t believe he treated them right. I think he had people in his ear to cut corners with finances concerning them which may have caused a rift between them.  I looked drastically online for photos of his kids with his parents. I couldn’t find any.  I also found it disturbing that there was an alleged dispute with his parents concerning purchasing them a house to the point that the parents placed rings that he gave them up for auction. I mean what was up with that? Why was there this type of discord with a man that was financially well off. Something is wrong with this picture and I don’t think the problem was Kobe parents as alleged in some of these online sources.

snippet.textDisplay:
As I was scrolling on my phone
I came across an article that read
"Kobe Bryant was in an helicopter crash
And he is dead"

I was like
This can't be
Not Kobe...
No he...

He's not gone
It Ain't true...it ain't true
Then I turned to ESPN
It was all over the news

9/26 was the day
Our world lost a giant
and his precious jewel
daughter Gianna Bryant

Weeping may endure for a night
Yet God shall wipe away every tear
Our prayers are with you Lady Vanessa
From very far and from so near

Take comfort in knowing
Time spent was enjoyed with Love
Now your two angels
Are watching from above

They're #2 & #24
Arrayed in purple & gold
Heaven just got a lot brighter
With these two beautiful souls

And like a packed arena
In our hearts there will always be a crowd
Chanting "Kobe" "Kobe"
You sure did do the NBA proud

....May the Lord continue to comfort the Bryant family. My deepest condolences for all concerned.

snippet.textDisplay: First, I feel so bad for the families that lost loved ones on that helicopter.  And here, I feel very badly for Jerry West.  You can tell he genuinely loved Kobe like a son.  His heart is breaking.  Mr. West seems so genuine and real.  For his own personal fame and fortune, he seems like a very good-natured, caring man.  I also think about the Altobelli’s surviving 16 year old daughter.  Imagine losing your younger sister and your mom and dad all at once at such a young age!  How does that poor child recover from that?  She’s in high school and should be enjoying the fun of life with friends and family in a carefree environment.  I really pray for that child.  She has an older brother.  He’s in his late 20s.  I’m sure he’ll be there for her as will hopefully aunts and uncles.  But, oh my gosh, that poor girl.

snippet.textDisplay:
The Canadian Senate unanimously passed a bill to combat organ trafficking on October 23, 2018.

“The bill amends the criminal code to create new offenses in relation to trafficking in human organs and tissue,” said bill sponsor Senator Salma Ataullahjan at a press conference.

Sen. Ataullahjan said that the bill, S-240, “amends the Immigration and Refugee Protection Act to provide that a permanent resident or foreign national is inadmissible to Canada if the minister of citizenship and immigration is of the opinion that they have engaged in any activities related to trafficking in human organs and tissue.”
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: My LORD! I truly understand the hurt and pain everyone is experiencing right now! My only brother passed away in 2013 and then 5 years later my son unexpectedly passed away as well. My heart cries for this tremendous loss of Kobe, his daughter, and all the other passengers on board! To know the pain the families are going through is heart breaking! His Wife, daughters, family members and all those who loved and respected Kobe Bryant. We never know why certain things happen and the impact of hurt and pain is so great but, I do know that God is a God of Love, Peace and comfort and in the days ahead I know God will soothe the pain and heal the broken hearted. They say time heals all wounds” but, in the almost 2 years my son has been gone I can tell you that the wounds heal but, the hurt and pain of him not being here still remains. My Prayers strongly goes out to Vanessa and their daughters, his parents and all who love him 🕊🙏🏽❤️
